Rule ID: GOV-001
Category: Governance & Access
Risk Level: High
Applies To: All SACCOs

Rule Description:
No single user should both create and approve a loan.

Why This Matters:
Prevents fraud and meets good governance practices.

Trigger Condition:
If loan.created_by == loan.approved_by

System Action:
- Block approval
- Raise critical alert
- Log evidence

Recommended Remediation:
Assign a second officer to approve the loan.

Evidence Collected:
- User IDs
- Loan ID
- Timestamp
